<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93000948/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """The assessment procedure for the progressive evaluation will be as follows:
One midterm exam including the first 4 chapters counting 30% of the final mark has to be completed. The student will have to solve a certain number of theoretical / practical issues similar to those contents of the practices and lectures. A minimum mark (3.5) is required.
One second term exam including the last chapters from 5 to 7 counting 30% of the final mark has to be completed. The student will have to solve a certain number of theoretical / practical issues similar to those contents of the practices and lectures. A minimum mark (3.5) is required.
A report including all requested exercises, counting 40% of the final mark.
The assessment procedure for the global evaluation, as well as the extraordinary examination, will be as follows:
A final exam counting 60% of the final mark has to be completed. The student will have to solve a certain number of theoretical / practical issues similar to those contents of the practices and lectures.
A report including all requested exercises, counting 40% of the final mark.
Any assessment or report may require a complementary oral assessment by the professor in order to validate that the task has been done by the student without help. According to the current assessment norms at UPM, if academic fraud is detected on any assessment, the student(s) will receive a grade of zero in the final grade of the examination to which the assessment belonged (ordinary or extraordinary)."""@es ;
